                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 90.&#8212;<name type="person"
                                                key="xxx">Private Perley J. Blodget</name>, <name
                                                type="organization" key="xxx">Co. H, 5th Wis.
                                                Vols.</name>; age 21 ; was admitted <date
                                                type="admit" when="1864-10-17">October 17,
                                                1864</date>. Diagnosis&#8212;remittent fever.
                                        Died <date type="death" when="1864-11-01">November 1</date>.
                                                <hi rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination
                                        forty-eight hours after death: Eight ounces of serum in
                                        right and two ounces in left pleural sac, one ounce in
                                        pericardium and a pint in the abdominal cavity. Spleen soft,
                                        dark, weighing about two pounds; liver and kidneys normal;
                                        Peyer's patches in the lower ileum, and the solitary
                                        follicles in the c&#230;cum and upper colon much
                                        thickened and ulcerated; mucous membrane of colon
                                                inflamed.&#8212;<hi rend="italic"><name
                                                  type="hospital" key="187">Second Division
                                                        Hospital</name>, <name type="place">Alexandria, Va.</name></hi></p>
                        
